gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 132, Cavaliers 123
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bulls defeated the Cavaliers, 132-123, in 2OT. DeMar DeRozan (35 points, 17-19 FT, 10 rebounds, five assists) led four Chicago players with double-doubles (Nikola Vucevic 24 points, 13 rebounds, five assists; Andre Drummond 17 points, 26 rebounds; Coby White  14 points, 12 assists) as Chicago defeated Cleveland for the first time since March 26, 2022. Evan Mobley (25 points, 13 rebounds, four blocks) and Darius Garland (23 points) led Cleveland as Caris LeVert added 14 points, seven rebounds, and a career-high 15 assists. Chicago moves to 28-31 as Cleveland is now 38-20.
